sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser Client
    participant Proxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant IdP as OIDC Provider /<br/>OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>Configurable Port
    participant Redis as Redis (optional)<br/>6379/TCP TLS

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: Browser-Based OAuth2/OIDC Login

    Browser->>Proxy: GET /oauth2/start<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Proxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to IdP<br/>authorization endpoint
    Browser->>IdP: GET /authorize<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>User credentials
    IdP->>Browser: 302 Redirect with<br/>authorization code + state
    Browser->>Proxy: GET /oauth2/callback<br/>HTTPS/443, auth code + CSRF state
    Proxy->>IdP: POST /token<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Client credentials + auth code
    IdP-->>Proxy: ID Token + Access Token
    Proxy->>Redis: Store session (optional)<br/>TCP/TLS 6379
    Redis-->>Proxy: OK
    Proxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to app<br/>Set-Cookie: encrypted session

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 2: Bearer Token API Request (JWT / sha256~ / ext_authz)

    participant APIClient as API Client
    APIClient->>Proxy: ANY /* or GET /oauth2/auth<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer token
    alt JWT Token
        Proxy->>IdP: GET /.well-known/jwks.json<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
        IdP-->>Proxy: JWKS keys
    else OpenShift sha256~ Token
        Proxy->>IdP: GET /apis/user.openshift.io/v1/users/~<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer token
        IdP-->>Proxy: User info
    end
    Proxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>Injected headers:<br/>X-Forwarded-User, X-Forwarded-Email
    Upstream-->>Proxy: Response
    Proxy-->>APIClient: Response (or 202 for ext_authz)

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 3: Kubernetes Service Account Token Validation

    participant K8sSA as K8s SA Client
    K8sSA->>Proxy: ANY /*<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer K8s SA token
    Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS (in-cluster CA)<br/>Proxy's own SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Proxy: TokenReview result<br/>(authenticated: true/false)
    Proxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>X-Forwarded-User: system:serviceaccount:ns:name
    Upstream-->>Proxy: Response
    Proxy-->>K8sSA: Response

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 4: Sign-Out with OAuthAccessToken Deletion (OpenShift)

    Browser->>Proxy: GET /oauth2/sign_out<br/>HTTPS/443, Session cookie
    Proxy->>K8sAPI: DELETE /apis/oauth.openshift.io/v1/<br/>oauthaccesstokens/{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, User's Bearer token
    K8sAPI-->>Proxy: 200 OK
    Proxy->>Redis: Delete session (optional)<br/>TCP/TLS 6379
    Redis-->>Proxy: OK
    Proxy->>Browser: Clear cookie + redirect<br/>to IdP end_session_endpoint
